	<Title>
		Recipe: Zesty tomato soup
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Zesty tomato soup &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		2
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Tomatoes are a good source of lycopene, an antioxidant that may help protect against cancer and cardiovascular disease. Lycopene is most plentiful in red tomatoes and is best absorbed when the tomatoes have been cooked. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
In a saucepan, add the soup and milk. Whisk together until smooth. Warm over medium heat about 7 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add in the chopped tomato and herbs. Cook an additional 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Ladle even amounts into individual bowls and garnish each serving with 1 tablespoon croutons and 1 1/2 teaspoons Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 can (10.5 ounces) condensed low-sodium, low-fat tomato soup&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 can (10.5 ounces) filled with fat-free milk&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 medium tomato, chopped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil or cilantro&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 tablespoons croutons&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon freshly grated Parmesan cheese &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
